From: retropangui-c5 build <build@retropangui-c5>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: aml-card: use dev_err_probe() for EPROBE_DEFER

aml_card_dai_link_of() logs a dev_err() every time
snd_soc_of_get_dai_link_codecs() returns -EPROBE_DEFER (-517), which
happens routinely while the t9015 audio codec hasn't finished probing
yet - confirmed on real hardware: ~20 of these fire in a row during
every boot (19s-22s), all before the codec finally probes
successfully at ~40.9s and the card comes up fine. EPROBE_DEFER is a
normal "retry later" signal, not an error - use the standard
dev_err_probe() helper (already used elsewhere in this kernel's
sound/soc tree, e.g. axg-fifo.c/aiu.c) so EPROBE_DEFER logs at debug
level and only genuine errors still show as ERROR.

---
 common_drivers/sound/soc/amlogic/auge/card.c | 9 +++++++--
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/common_drivers/sound/soc/amlogic/auge/card.c b/common_drivers/sound/soc/amlogic/auge/card.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/common_drivers/sound/soc/amlogic/auge/card.c
+++ b/common_drivers/sound/soc/amlogic/auge/card.c
@@ -981,8 +981,13 @@
 	ret = snd_soc_of_get_dai_link_codecs(dev, codec, dai_link);

 	if (ret < 0) {
-		dev_err(dev, "%s, error dai-link idx:%d, error getting codec dai, ret %d\n",
-				__func__, idx, ret);
+		/* EPROBE_DEFER fix: codec not probed yet is a normal retry,
+		 * not an error - use dev_err_probe() so EPROBE_DEFER logs at
+		 * debug level and only real errors show as ERROR (this was
+		 * spamming ~20 ERROR lines every single boot). */
+		ret = dev_err_probe(dev, ret,
+				"%s, error dai-link idx:%d, error getting codec dai\n",
+				__func__, idx);
 		goto dai_link_of_err;
 	}

